'''Boneau/Bryan-Brown''', Inc. is a [[public relations]] company based in [[Manhattan]], [[New York City|New York]], United States, largely supporting [[Broadway theatre]] productions as a theatrical [[press agency]].<ref>{{IBDB name|name=Boneau / Bryan-Brown|id=1060}}.</ref>
The company was formed by the partnership of [[Chris Boneau]]<ref>{{IBDB name|name=Chris Boneau|id=71423}}.</ref> and [[Adrian Bryan-Brown]]<ref>{{IBDB name|name=Adrian Bryan-Brown|id=71422}} </ref> in 1991. Broadway productions supported include, among hundreds, the musical ''[[Guys and Dolls]]'' in 1992.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://soundcloud.com/american-theatre-wing/episode-236 |title=Adrian Bryan-Brown | publisher=American Theatre Wing|work=Downstage Center|date=September 28, 2009 | accessdate=October 2, 2011}} </ref> The company initially represented the rock musical ''[[Spider-Man: Turn Off the Dark]]'' which finally opened on Broadway in 2011.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.playbill.com/news/article/141223-PR-Firm-Boneau-Bryan-Brown-Resigns-From-Spider-Man-Turn-Off-the-Dark-Account | title=PR Firm Boneau/Bryan-Brown Resigns From Spider-Man Turn Off the Dark Account | first=Andrew | last=Gans | work=[[Playbill]] | date=15 July 2010 | accessdate=October 2, 2011 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111012170034/http://www.playbill.com/news/article/141223-PR-Firm-Boneau-Bryan-Brown-Resigns-From-Spider-Man-Turn-Off-the-Dark-Account | archivedate=12 October 2011 | df= }}</ref>
