[[File:modelhome.jpg|thumb|Build Now Model Home]]
'''Build Now''' is a [[non-profit organization]] located in [[New Orleans]], Louisiana, that works with clients whose homes were destroyed as a result of [[Hurricane Katrina]] to build new homes on their property.<ref>http://www.djcgulfcoast.com/item.cfm?recID=12373</ref> Build Now was founded by New Orleans native William Monaghan and is now directed by his daughter Tess Monaghan.<ref>http://www.neworleanscitybusiness.com/viewStory.cfm?recID=33804{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Build Now is a licensed and insured residential contractor, and constructs site-built, elevated houses that reflect the style and quality of traditional New Orleans architecture.<ref>http://www.buildnownola.com</ref> Since 2008, Build Now has built new homes for nearly a dozen New Orleans families, with 7 houses currently under construction around the city. Build Now moved their first resident home in January 2009 and have moved several other families back home since.<ref>http://blog.nola.com/mollyreid/2009/05/hgio_0502hgxx_green_living_483.html</ref> Hundreds of additional families have benefitted from the organization’s educational programs on topics such as <ref>http://www.nola.com/news/index.ssf/2009/03/fema_extends_deadline_for_home.html</ref> how to obtain the money you need to elevate your home, how to improve your [[credit score]] and qualify for a loan, and how to improve the indoor air quality of your home.<ref>http://www.buildnownola.com/events/</ref>
Build Now offers 14 different house plans that range in price from $105,000 to $165,000.<ref>http://www.neworleanscitybusiness.com/viewStory.cfm?recID=30790{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The designs mix traditional New Orleans architecture with basic green features such as energy-efficient wall construction, heavy-duty roof insulation and large windows to reduce reliance on electric lights.
