{{Campaignbox Crusades Battles}}

The [[Crusades|Crusader]] fortress of [[Caesarea]] fell to the [[Mamluk]]s in 1265.  In 1251, [[Louis IX of France|Louis IX]] had fortified the city, ordering the construction of high walls (parts of which are still standing) and a deep moat. However, strong walls could not keep out the Mamluk sultan [[Baybars]], who ordered his troops to scale the walls in several places simultaneously, enabling them to penetrate the city.

